private set intersection, secure data mining,
and more. In this paper we introduce fresh constant‑round two‑party computation (2 PC) protocols targeting both tasks. These constructions follow an online/offline model. For 32‑bit values, the online traffic required by our equality test amounts to just 76 bits—about 1 % of ABYT’s overhead—while the secure comparison consumes 384 bits, roughly 5 % of the ABY benchmark.
